---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="How I Choose What to Watch: A Film Philosophy | Jevan Goldsmith"
  description="How Jevan Goldsmith picks films, what he looks for in great cinema, and why movies are a fast way to live a life that is not your own."
  canonical="https://jevangoldsmith.com/movie-philosophy.html"
>
<style slot="head" is:inline set:html={`
    .page-header .container, main.container { max-width: none; padding: 0 1rem; }
    .reading-philosophy-content { max-width: none; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; }
    @media (min-width: 769px) { .page-header .container, main.container { padding: 0 3rem; } }
`} />
<header class="page-header">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>My Movie Philosophy</h1>
            <p>How I choose what to watch, what I look for in a film, and why movies matter to me.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <article class="reading-philosophy-content">
            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>Why I Watch</h2>
                <p>Movies are the fastest way to live a life that is not mine. The best ones expand my sense of what is possible, sharpen my taste, and leave me with images and questions I cannot shake.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>How I Choose What to Watch</h2>
                <p>I lean on directors I trust, friends with sharp taste, and a small set of critics who write honestly. If a film keeps surfacing in conversations with people I respect, it moves up the queue.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>What I Look For</h2>
                <p>Specificity over spectacle. A clear point of view. Craft in writing, framing, sound, and editing. I would rather watch a small film made with conviction than a big one made by committee.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>How I Watch</h2>
                <p>One film at a time, phone away, lights down. I log every watch on Letterboxd and write a short review when something is worth coming back to. The note matters more than the rating.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>Where to Go Next</h2>
                <p>Browse my recent watches and reviews, then follow the threads into the directors and writers behind the films that stuck.</p>
                <p><a href="/movies.html">See my recent watches</a></p>
            </section>

            <div class="back-to-books">
                <a href="/movies.html" class="back-link">&larr; Back to My Movie Reviews</a>
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
</Base>
